# Python UDFs

## When no built-in fits — two paths

- **`@udf(returnType)`** — decorator for the DataFrame API
- **`spark.udf.register(name, func, returnType)`** — callable from `spark.sql(...)`

## The cost is real

- Every row crosses the **JVM ↔ Python boundary twice** → **10–100× slower** than a built-in

## A Catalyst black box

- **No predicate pushdown** across it (whole column read first)
- **No column pruning** · **no null safety** (`None` may crash it) · **no plan-time type check**
- **Exhaust built-ins, higher-order functions, and Pandas UDFs first.**
